In regard to the List of York Service Books, it may be worth while adding a short account of a unique volume, “Expositio Hymnorum et Sequentiarum,” published by Wansfort at York, 1507. The volume is in possession of ΜΓ. Kerslake, of Bristol, who very kindly placed it in my hands. It is not an exposition of hymns and sequenoes of the York Use, though doubtless intended to be used in the Diocese, but identical with that accord- ing to the Use of Sarum. The words “Secundum usum Sarum'' have been omitted, and new title-peges, colophons, and intro- ductory letters inserted. The volume does not appear to have been intended in any way for liturgica] use, but as a school· book, as will be seen from the introductory letters, which, with the titles and colophona, I subjoin. I have added part of the Exposition of the Sequence for st. Catharine, which will give a clear idea of the character of the Exposition.
